The past month and a half have just been insane. I have no idea where to start. I have a million pictures that I would like to post to show you what I mean. But as of right now, I dont have the time. I've become closer to a few people, and find myslef becoming distant with more. That is what scares me. At the end of April/beginning of May, I will post all of my lovely pictures of my escapades. It will include hair dying, europe, concerts, cvs trips, the fair, lots of school, potentially the beach, and everything else. I promise. Just for your amusement. I have been so busy, my head is spinning, but in a god way. These past few days I have been super super sick. I havent eaten since saturday morning and to be honest, I dont care to. I need a shower. I'm feeling a bit better so I'm definately going to school tommorow. To be honest, even if I feel bad I think I'll go to school. A girl can only take so much of lying on the couch watching daytime tv. Life is good and I am content. I love everyone and the world at this point. Check back in a few weeks. Lets hope this elation lasts.

Ok, so I am posting pictures and putting it under a cut because I just learned how. Oh how exciting. So yeah, these are my pictures for the past few days. So Friday I skipped 5th period. IVE NEVER SKIPPED BEFORE. It was a lot of fun. Probably too much. It was way too easy and I am afraid I am going to do it too often. I only dis it to avoid this scary jamaican dude that keeps hitting on me despite my polite declines and flat out telling him I have a boyfriend (LIE). But anyways, it was funnnnn. Then, friday Carolyn, Caitlyn and I went out to dinner at Canton. I'm kind of disapointed with myself, I only have one picture. at least its cute. And last but not least I did comunity service on saturday with Laurel and Allison, even though we didnt do anything but give each other war-paint instead of painting the walls like we were supposed to. 23 days until the MCR concert! Last night I went to Dolphin with Caitlyn, Erik, and Israel and then to Erik's house. Amazingly fun.

It went from 2 to 4 to 5 to 4 to 3. Now, I have no idea where anything stands between my friends. Friends is the wrong word. These guys are the family I never had. And the worst part, the very worst part, is that I feel so betrayed. So betrayed. And it hurts. It just really hurts. I dont know how long I can take all of these platonic heartbreaks.

I made chocolate chip ccokies. And. They. Are. So. Good. Im going to Caitlyns tonight so yeahhhhhh. Oh, and I got a HIM poster yesterday (yay for ville vallo!), and earings. And today I FINALLY bought the old MCR cd. Love it. Farewell my doodlebops.

Well. Erik is going to Tampa, Caitlyn is at here dads, Paul is attched to his computer, Israel is home. And so am I. My mom is making me stay home because My brothers are having people over, and my parents are going out, so I must suffer. So Im just going to stay up late, eat pizza, watch movies, take a bubble bath, maybe do my nails, you know, the usual things you do when your stuck home on a friday night. I wish I was going out tonight.

Well Well Well. Its fourth of july today and I am in NC with my favorite birthmark mole-ster, Caitlyn Rose. I havent updated in forever due to the fact that my comouter at home is utterly retarded. I've grown half an inch. Kind of sad because I thought I was done growing. I got a new atv. Very nice. Last night Caitlyn and I watched freddy got fingered, which is quite possibly one of the funniest movies of all time. We are going to shoot of fireworks tonight. The illegal kind that you can only buy in south carolina. As much as I dont like the actual city of miami, I miss the people in it. Well, the ones Im friends with anyway. And Its only been 3 days. I got hit on my a boy. A cute one at that. He was tall with long blonde hair, and heres the best part, HE WASNT WEARING SANDALS!  as you all know, I have a serious foot problem, I dont like feet much, so this was a big plus. And him not being a hillbilly was nice too. But I wont see him again. Which I suppose is good, because I dont want to be in ant kind of romantic relationship right now. It makes things too complex. So yep, I will update when I can. Until then. Stay classy San Diego.





Oh yes, and I have a myspace now. Feell free. Its under slapdash227@aol.com

Havent updated in a while due to my internet not working. Im at Laurens house now. I spent the day with Bella and Lauren. Not much new. Stil going to post pictures that I got from today and about a week ago. I will try to anyway.

Yeah, thats me and my dad. He's rad. And I suck I rhyming. We play charades when we go scuba diving, he's tought me to drive, and that every other driver on the road is either an idiot or a dumbass. He fixes my shower. He doesnt like me to have boys in my room when the door is closed. He is convinced that I am too good for every guy that I go out with, and that they will break my heart. We cook dinner sometimes together. I know that if I had black hair and a mustache, we'd look exactly alike. He tells me that I dress weird. I tell him that when he was my age, his socks were twice the length of his shorts. He saves me from my mother. We talk. Today, when we were coming back from diving, it started to storm. Not just any storm, a huge lighting storm. And here we were sitting in a 31 foot boat in the middle of the marina with no place to dock. My mom and brothers got off. I stayed on the boat. So me and my dad sat in the rain, thunder, and lightning for an hour and a half. I didnt want him to sit out there alone. So anyways. Thanks Dad. Thanks for being there for me, protecting me, and putting up with my crap. And letting me know that not everyone will be as easygoing as you are.  Thanks for treating me like a princess when I was a little girl, and never quite getting out of the habit. Thank you for everything Dad. Thank you and Happy Fathers Day.

The world's termites outweigh the world's humans 10 to 1.

While in some countries the penalty for driving while intoxicated can be death (yes, death), in Uruguay intoxication is a legal excuse for having an accident while driving. "Please believe me officer, I really was drunk." 

The phrase "raining cats and dogs" originated in 17th Century England. During heavy downpours of rain, many of these poor animals unfortunately drowned and their bodies would be seen floating in the rain torrents that raced through the streets. The situation gave the appearance that it had literally rained "cats and dogs" and led to the current expression.

So Israel's mom came and took us home and he walked me to my door because my house is scary from the outside when you are alone at night. So today, Brandon is at graduation. Yay for the class of '05. Im going to miss you guys! And I have to go to my mom's best friends son's graduation party. And yes, its my punishment. But I'll take one day of torture over a whole summer of grounding.

wow. home sweet home. I hate going on vacation for a whole week with my family. as mean as that sounds, as spoiled as it makes me sound, its just too much closeness. I cant take it. It was a horribly long week, so I'll sum it up for you. Heres the highlights/lowlights/main points.....
* On the plane there, I thought that we were going to crash
* my mom and dad snore LOUD. I couldnt sleep
* after a few days, I had to resort to heavily caffinated tea from Starbucks
* I am now a caffine-addict
* we went to hershey pennsylvania, where they make the chocolate (definately highlight)
* I relized just how much I hate my brothers
* I didnt have my tea, and was in a horrid mood for the whole day
* Next day, I had an emotional breakdown (not from the tea!) I spent half the day locked in the hotel bathroom sobbing uncontrolably
* I was sick that whole week, then it got REALLY bad, I felt so horrid
* On the plane back, there was A LOT of turbulence
* I was sitting in the back, so everybody was running to the bathroom (which was 5 feet away) to blow chunks
* I thought that we were going to crash
* I relized that I want to and have to get over my INSANE fear of flying
* got off the plane 
* retreived my luggage
* came home
* brushed my teeth, washed my face, went to sleep fully dressed

thats it. Today I wake up at 6:30, because I forgot to turn my alarm back on. Im scrabbling looking for something to wear. my suitcase is dumped out on the floor. I couldnt find anything. I finally found what must be the one clean outfit I own. I will have to do laundry today. So anyway, I rush rush rush. Then I go outside in the humidity, and my hair, which i spent 10 minutes of my precious 25 minutes doing, got completely messed up. But it is definately good to be home. See, here, I can lock myself in my room. I only leave for food, the computer, to go to school, and to go out. I have my own connecting bathroom, so thats not a problem. And in the words of Judy Garland, "There's no place like home." Love....

Today was peachy keen. I woke up at Caitlyn's. Then I helped her clean her room then came home. When I got home, I cleaned my fishies (Dr. Frank n Furter and Eric Draven) bowls. Next thing I knew, I was 12:30 and I was not ready for Erin's Party! So I called Alex, she was going to come get me. We ended up being there at 2:30. The party started at 1. We COMPLETELY missed the suprise. But it was ok. We walked up to the beach. We passed Erin and she didnt even reognize us. So, being the girl that I am, jumped on her and gave her a big hug. Then we went to the party (which we had walked right by) and Joe said hi to us. Oh man... did Joe grow up since the last time I saw him. I know that if he reads this, I am going to be SO embarrased. But I also know that I will probably never see him again, and even if I do, what are the odds that he will read this? So anyway, Joe was hot. So me and Alex were kind of outcasts at this party. We only knew Joe, Erin, and each other. I KNEW other people, but they had no idea who I was (dont you hate that?). Everyone was playing on the playground. Then Erin made us come to the beach with her. Me and Alex went in the water while everyone else played volleyball. Then we found Alex's mom and her sister Stephanie. So we hung out with them for a bit. Then we went to have cake. Joe started throwing it. By the end of the "cake fight" everyone was completely coved in chocolate cake. Joe said "I am sooo tasty! who wants to lick the frosting off me?" hahaha, I did, but I refrained because my heart belongs to someone else (too bad he doesnt care if I'm alive or dead). Then me and Alex hung around there for a while, then went back to her mom and Stephanie. Erin came over to talk to us. I think her mom felt bad that we were alone, off to the side and told Erin to pay attention to us, but whatever. Then we left. Oh and when Joe said goodbye to us, his girlfriend gave us the WORST look. And I know it's a cliche, but oh man, if looks could kill.... I'd be buried already. Like she was jealous of us or something! Come on! She was pretty and thin! I wish I could say the same for myself. All we did was say goodbye! She must have some SERIOUS insecurities. So we left and went to Borders so Alex could pick up a book. We got fries from Burger King, then they dropped me off at home and here I sit. Being that all I've had all day was a bit of french fries and a small piece of chocolate cake, I'm pretty hungry. I also feel VERY gross. I need a shower so bad. I need to wash off all of this greasy sunscreen. Oh yes, and I'm leaving tommorow at nine AM for washington DC. I wont be back until sunday. SO I may or may not get another entry in. My only way of communication is if you send me a text message on my cell phone. SOOO, dont bother calling, I wont pick it up because of the HEAVY roaming charges. So just send a message. I love you all and have a nice spring break.
